      • isRoot

        boolean isRoot()
        This method is used to check if the current node is the root of the tree.
        Returns:
        true if the node is root, false otherwise.

      • isTerminal

        boolean isTerminal()
        This method is used to check if the current node is a terminal node of the game tree.
        Returns:
        true if this is a terminal node, false otherwise.

      • isNature

        boolean isNature()
        This method is used to check if the current node is a nature node.
        Returns:
        true if the current node is nature, false otherwise.

      • isPlayer1

        boolean isPlayer1()
        This method is used to check if this node belong to player1, meaning that it represents a choice for the first player playing the game. Note that the labels of the descendants of this node should be used by player2.
        Returns:
        true if the node belong to player1, false otherwise

      • isPlayer2

        boolean isPlayer2()
        This method is used to check if this node belong to player2, meaning that it represents a choice for the second player playing the game. Note that the labels of the descendants of this node should be used by player1.
        Returns:
        true if the node belong to player2, false otherwise

      • getOutcome

        java.lang.String getOutcome()
        If this is a terminal node, this returns a String representation of the outcome represented by this node. If the node is not terminal the behavior of this method is not specified.
        Returns:
        String representation of the outcome represented by this node (if the node is terminal).

      • getAncestor

        GameNode getAncestor()
              throws GameNodeDoesNotExistException
        This method returns the ancestor of the current node if one exists and generates an exception when executed over a node without an ancestor (the root node).
        Returns:
        the GameNode that is directly above the current one in the tree
        Throws:
        GameNodeDoesNotExistException - if the current node is the root of a game tree.

      • getDescendant

        GameNode getDescendant(java.lang.String label)
                throws GameNodeDoesNotExistException
        This method returns a descendant of the current node identified by label if that node exists.
        Parameters:
        label - The label of the target descendant node.
        Returns:
        an instance of GameNode representing the descendant node if it exists
        Throws:
        GameNodeDoesNotExistException - if the requested node is not a descendant of the current node or does not exists.

      • getChildrenLabels

        java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String> getChildrenLabels()
        This method exposes an iterator over the labels of all direct descendants of the current node.
        Returns:
        an Iterator over String, that contains the labels of direct descendant nodes.

      • getChildren

        java.util.Iterator<GameNode> getChildren()
        This method exposes an iterator over all direct descendants of the current node.

      • numberOfChildren

      • getLabel

        java.lang.String getLabel()
        Returns the label of the edge that allows to navigate from the ancestor node to the current one.
        Returns:
        a String containing the label of the direct edge that allows to reach the current node in the tree.

      • getWeight

        double getWeight()
        If the ancestor to the current node is nature, this represents the probability of reaching the current node.
        Returns:
        the probability of reaching the current node if the ancestor is nature. The return value is unspecified for nodes whose ancestor is not nature.

        Returns a string representation of the current node.

      • getPayoffP1

        int getPayoffP1()

        payoff

      • getPayoffP2
